scene_description_enriched: The scene depicts a martyrdom. A haloed figure, likely a saint, stands naked and bound, pierced by numerous arrows. Several figures surround him, some holding bows and arrows, suggesting they are the executioners. One figure wears a crown, indicating a person of authority. In the background, stylized architectural elements and foliage are visible. The overall composition suggests a violent act of persecution and death, interpreted as the martyrdom of Saint Sebastian.
